<TITLE> Taskforce proposed to help next govt weather recession fallout </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 5 (bdnews24.com)  Civil society members on Friday suggested a taskforce was formed to help the incoming elected government to face emerging financial crisis on a continual basis, private think-tank CPD said in press statement. The suggestion was floated at the CPD office where the civil society members met to discuss the impact of ongoing financial crisis and global recession on Bangladesh economy. The taskforce would provide the incoming government concrete recommendations and actionable agendas to address the emerging situation. CPD, Bangladesh Institute of Development Studies and other relevant stakeholders also would share with the taskforce some special responsibilities and suggest appropriate policy interventions to the government. Professor Mostafijur Rahman, executive director of CPD, Dr M Asaduzzaman, research director of BIDS, M Anisul Huq, Khushi Kabir, co-ordinator, Nijera Kori and others were present at the meeting. Professor Rehman Sobhan, chairman, CPD, moderated the meeting
